# Coding Procedures

- ALWAYS look at other functions and other parts of the code to see how the new code suggested will affect old code.
- Focus on code relavent to the task
- Do not touch code that is unrelated to the task
- Write test for all major functionality
- Avoid making changes to the pattern and architechture of how a feature works, unless specially asked to
- Always think about what other areas of the methods and areas of the code might be affected by code changes. 
